{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The authenticated v1.19 record and committed reader chain establish the terminal event as an engineering custody defect: the public outer-finalized manifest was valid at two links, but the closure's generic JSON reread silently expected one. No closure, binding, formal authority, or scientific conclusion is inferred from that failure."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.20 closure captures the finalized producer manifest under an explicit two-link contract, canonical-parses and hashes that same payload, requires byte equality with the public verifier's object, and no longer performs a loose manifest digest reread. Both binding stable-file readers now require every caller to state link custody explicitly."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Production-chain regressions drive the real create_development_closure seam through a valid outer-finalized terminal and reject one-link, three-link, symlinked, in-read-mutated, and public-verifier-divergent manifests. A selective sha256_file trap proves the bound manifest digest comes from the captured bytes; restoring implicit one-link custody breaks the positive path."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The remaining live producer-terminal consumers were audited across artifact verification, operator capture, closure/archive construction, preformal reopening, launch authorization, independent artifact audit, and adjudication. Precommit readers require one link, outer-finalized readers require two, and no additional finalized-manifest one-link mismatch was found."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Scientific continuity is exact: all 17 declared scientific protocol blocks equal the sealed v1.19 predecessor, the four kernel source digests are unchanged, and formal-binding v10 and raw-result v9 differ only in version-scoped protocol and fresh-seed identities. The model, learning, planning, metrics, thresholds, budgets, controls, and audit-capacity contract remain frozen."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The active protocol directly pins the exact sealed v1.19 protocol digest. Independent SHA-256 reconstruction confirmed both fresh master tuples, central-verifier and independent-auditor parity for all 19 predecessor tuples, 10 unique current masters and 1,360 streams, 190 unique prior masters and 25,840 streams, and zero overlap in every declared collision class."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"One reviewed wheel supplies separate fresh QA and runtime environments. The regenerated protocol-1.20 lock exactly verifies the untouched 45-row runtime closure, QA and runtime share the same Prospect distribution identity, all 51 installed executable Python files equal the live reviewed source, and QA-only test tools are absent from runtime."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"resolved","severity":"minor","summary":"The plan and runbook bind fresh v1.20 namespaces, environments, seal, review, producer, operator, binding, rehearsal, formal, audit, and adjudication paths; all exact lifecycle paths were absent during review. The mandatory focused gate explicitly names the repaired closure-seam tests before any runtime seal or outcome path may be created."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"resolved","severity":"minor","summary":"Independent final validation observed an exact three-row protocol seal, a passing protocol verifier, clean Ruff and diff checks, clean 33-file core and 13-file boundary mypy gates, 100 passing fresh-QA mandatory integration cases, and 23 passing preserved-preformal consumer cases."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The declared assurance model remains local exact-byte, stable-file, cooperative-lock, and append-only custody with tamper_resistant false. Acceptance does not claim protection from a privileged or same-principal hostile writer."},{"id":"F011","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"This review examined source, schemas, authenticated failure metadata, artifact identities, engineering custody, dependency closure, and test behavior without opening or reporting any prior or current scientific performance value."},{"id":"F012","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Prospective acceptance establishes that the repaired harness is coherent enough for one sealed attempt; it does not predict successful execution and supplies no evidence that any scientific endpoint or general Prospect capability will pass."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1685,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"48a08ea0fc0d0c72d5a79d8746f1d45dd8c6e291fd95f343d3e3ea42f84f9fee"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"},{"bytes":20656,"path":"bench/epistemic/runtime_lane.py","sha256":"d8f0c7a85be786c3a813ee1f169abcbc2791a642e46fba5978f7a1140cc50387"},{"bytes":278,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/SEALED_PROTOCOL.sha256","sha256":"82eefd0536ba0233973168481c7566babecbcd65e60da56f6ac2d8e7123e4f2b"},{"bytes":75,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/__init__.py","sha256":"0390d290f